content.description:
This provides access to the top of the cliff if you want to set up top ropes. Start up a 5.2 dihedral just left of the slab start for

Purple Jokers

. Traverse up and right passing across the base of the

Purple Joker

crack to a final rock step (5.2) that leads to a rim.

This is a high quality crack route. Despite the precarious look of the large block in the roof, it isn't moving. It took several sledgy hits, and it didn't budge. We cleaned lots of the loose rocks out of the crack.

Start up an overhanging hand crack in a dihedral. This is fun. The crack then widens to a no hands rest in a pod under the roof. Take a breath, and traverse left out of the roof to a wide crack that narrows to tight hands to the top. Fantastic.
content.protection: BD #0.4-3 C4s. You can bring an optional #4 for down low and an optional #5 for the top. Bring 100 feet of webbing for an anchor at a tree 50 feet back or a few extra #1s for a gear anchor at the lip.

content.description: Too bad the finger crack isn't longer! Start up a 5.4 slab to a stance at the base of an off finger crack. Climb up the crack for 12 feet to the rim. Hopefully you're finger locks are dialed. Belay off wide gear.
content.protection: Two BD #0.5s for the climb and #3-4s for a gear anchor at the top.
